door:26:26:52:52:data\maps\house.map:12:4:You return to your house.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
trigger:22:30:49:55:data\story\village_first_look.txt:once
door:66:66:82:82:data\maps\miller_house.map:12:4:You step into Doran Miller's tidy cottage.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:114:114:90:90:data\maps\reed_house.map:12:4:You step into the Reed sisters' flower-scented home.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:162:162:82:82:data\maps\tanner_house.map:12:4:You enter the Tanner home, warm with herbs and soup.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:152:152:46:46:data\maps\mayor_house.map:25:4:You step into Mayor Holloway's sprawling house.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:34:34:20:20:data\maps\orphanage.map:39:20:You step into Yuri Orphanage, where every floorboard seems to remember a name.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:14:14:100:100:data\maps\worship_temple.map:14:2:You push through the stone temple door and into cool marble air.:misk\stonedoor.ogg:misk\stonedoor_activate.ogg:true:false
door:174:174:20:20:data\maps\shopping_center.map:1:20:You step into the shopping center, where voices, coin, and worry all compete for the same room.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:206:206:106:106:data\maps\village.map:204:106:The eastern gate stays shut.:misk\doorexit1.ogg:misk\dooractivate2.ogg:true:true:The exit from the village is locked due to strange events that might be related to the divine.
object:94:100:88:92:A low stone well. The water echoes softly below.:objects\rock1.ogg:misk\bump_stone.ogg
object:108:112:74:78:The village notice board is packed with supply requests, warnings, and a few personal messages folded twice.:objects\paper.ogg
object:48:52:78:82:A stack of chopped logs waits beside a splitting stump.:objects\table.ogg
object:10:14:94:98:A waist-high stone brazier burns in front of the temple steps, breathing out dry heat and old incense.:objects\rock1.ogg:misk\bump_stone.ogg
object:38:40:18:20:A painted wooden sign reads Yuri Orphanage. Someone has tied a faded ribbon around one corner.:objects\paper.ogg
object:164:168:18:20:A broad sign over the front reads Yuri Shopping Center in cheerful letters that have survived better years.:objects\paper.ogg
object:184:188:104:108:A pair of village supply crates sit beside the eastern gate, half unpacked and left in a hurry.:objects\table.ogg
npc:42:42:76:76:objects\npc.ogg:"If you're looking for the temple, keep following the north road till the air starts smelling like incense."
npc:126:126:72:72:objects\npc.ogg:"The shopping center's all the way down in the southeast now. Nobody can say it's crowded anymore."
npc:156:156:76:76:objects\npc.ogg:"The mayor likes his distance. Can't say the rest of us mind."
npc:178:178:100:100:objects\npc.ogg:"Gate's shut. Captain says nobody leaves till we know what the divine wants. I didn't ask what a divine is, and neither should you."
object:84:88:70:72:A weathered bench sits near the road, polished smooth by years of village gossip.:objects\bench.ogg
object:134:136:72:74:A battered trashcan rattles in the breeze with every loose scrap inside.:objects\trashcan.ogg
